{"vegetarian": true, "glutenFree": true, "title": "Mughlai Malai Kofta Curry", "veryPopular": false, "gaps": "no", "sourceUrl": "http://www.foodista.com/recipe/HKVP8LCX/mughlai-malai-kofta-curry", "sourceName": "Foodista", "vegan": false, "sustainable": false, "instructions": "<ol><li>Boil the potatoes, cool, peel and grate them.</li><li>Grate paneer.</li><li>Wash all green chillies, deseed and chop them fine.</li><li>Peel carrots,grate them, add peas and some water, boil them in microwave for 10 mins. Once done, remove excess by passing &amp; squeezing it through a muslin cloth.</li><li>Peel onions, cut them into halves and boil with a cup of water for ten minutes. Drain excess water, cool onions and grind them into a smooth paste. Set Aside.</li><li>In a bowl, mix mashed potatoes, paneer, some chopped green chillies, boiled carrot-peas, corn flour and salt. Mix well. Divide into 20-22 equal sized balls. Stuff  raisins &amp; cashew into them. Deep fry in hot oil until slightly golden brown. Drain and keep aside. Fry one kofta and check for binding, if it breaks, add a little more cornflour. Deep fry in hot oil.</li><li>OR BAKE in a 375F pre-heat oven, by arranging &amp; spraying oil on these koftas placing them on a cookie sheet wraped with aluminum foil,for 10 mins. Keep a close watch, with the help of tongs, turn them once they are slight brown on one side.</li><li>On the other side heat oil in a kadai, add shahjeera, boiled onion paste and cook for five minutes. Add ginger &amp; garlic, few chopped green chillies, coriander powder, cumin powder, turmeric powder, and salt. cook for a minute.</li><li>Add tomato puree and red chilli powder and cook on medium flame untill oil separates from gravy.</li><li>Add half&amp;half along with some water &amp; bring it to a boil and simmer for ten minutes on a slow flame. Stir occasionally.</li><li>Stir in fresh cream and garam masala powder.</li><li>Gently put all of these kofta's in the gravy when ready to serve. Simmer for another 2 mins and enjoy this rich, creamy gravy with Nan/Roti (Indian Flat Bread.)</li></ol>", "aggregateLikes": 1, "dairyFree": false, "extendedIngredients": [{"aisle": "Nuts", "unitLong": "cups", "amount": 0.125, "unitShort": "c", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "cup", "originalString": "1/8 cup cashews", "name": "cashews"}, {"aisle": "Spices and Seasonings", "unitLong": "teaspoons", "amount": 0.5, "unitShort": "t", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "teaspoon", "originalString": "1/2 teaspoon Red chilli powder", "name": "chilli powder"}, {"aisle": "Spices and Seasonings", "unitLong": "teaspoon", "amount": 1.0, "unitShort": "t", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "teaspoon", "originalString": "1 teaspoon Coriander powder", "name": "coriander powder"}, {"aisle": "Baking", "unitLong": "cups", "amount": 0.25, "unitShort": "c", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "cup", "originalString": "1/4 cup corn starch", "name": "corn starch"}, {"aisle": "Spices and Seasonings", "unitLong": "teaspoon", "amount": 1.0, "unitShort": "t", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "teaspoon", "originalString": "1 teaspoon cumin powder", "name": "cumin powder"}, {"aisle": "Spices and Seasonings", "unitLong": "teaspoon", "amount": 1.0, "unitShort": "t", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "teaspoon", "originalString": "1 teaspoon cumin seeds", "name": "cumin seeds"}, {"aisle": "Produce", "unitLong": "cups", "amount": 0.25, "unitShort": "c", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "cup", "originalString": "1/4 cup Fresh Cilantro, finely chopped", "name": "fresh cilantro"}, {"aisle": "Ethnic Foods", "unitLong": "teaspoon", "amount": 1.0, "unitShort": "t", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "teaspoon", "originalString": "1 teaspoon Garam Masala", "name": "garam masala"}, {"aisle": "Produce", "unitLong": "Tbsp", "amount": 1.0, "unitShort": "Tbsp", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "Tbsp", "originalString": "1 Tbsp, Garlic Paste", "name": "garlic paste"}, {"aisle": "Ethnic Foods", "unitLong": "Tbsp", "amount": 1.0, "unitShort": "Tbsp